Report: act_report¶

1 - Introduction¶

The goal of this project is to provide a student a hands-on example of how to gather, clean and analyse real data. "WeRateDogs" Twitter account with over 4 million followers that rates people's dogs with a humorous comment about the dog was selected as data source.

Project "Wrangling and Analyse Data" consist of following steps:

  • data gathering,
  • data assessment,
  • data cleaning,
  • data storing,
  • last but not least, data analysis and visualisation.

Let me walk you through them in more details below.

2 - Data wrangling¶

Data gathering process was split in 3 different sub-tasks: first, read 'twitter-archive-enhanced' file to Data Frame; second, read tweet image predictions tsv file by using request library; and third, collect additional tweet data using Twitter API. Due to technical issues with obtaining developer twitter account, I leveraged 'tweet-json.txt' file that containes additional data available through Twitter APIs and and read json file line by line to a Data Frame.

After saving each data Data Frame separately, I conducted visual and programmatic assessment to define tidiness ad quality issues. During visual assessment I was randomly viewing subsets of data frames and during programmatic assessment I was mainly using such methods as 'describe', 'info', 'sample' and etc.

Data assessment resulted in a list of quality and tidiness issues (16 in total, documented details can be found in 'wrangle_act.ipynb' file), that were tackled and resolved during cleaning process. Cleaned data was saved as 'twitter_archive_master.csv' file as per requirements and going forward was used for further analysis and visualisation.

3 - Data analysis and visualisation¶

After analysing cleaned data we can make share several insights:

  • According to processed data, tweets that has "pupper" dog stage have lower rating and lower retweet count on average compare to other dog stages. Max number of retweets falls on "doggo", closely followed by tweets with "pupper".
  • Top 5 most popular dog names within tweets are Charlie, Oliver, Cooper, Lucy, Penny.
  • Most popular dog breed in tweets is Golden Retriever, nevertheless Labrador Retrievres average rating is slightly higher compare to Golden Retriever.

  • After analysing sesonality of tweets data showed that original tweets are mostly posted on Monday-Wednesday and users are less active over weekend. Despite people are most activly posting on Mondays, Twitter users mostly retweeting tweets that are posted on Wednesdays.

4 - Conclusion¶

Twitter data contains vast range of interesting insights, so we encourage others to play Sherlock and try to find even more enlightments and clues!
